Pleased to announce I have the honor of speaking at the @dusablemuseum ‘The Color Is: Renaissance’ Symposium alongside many other incredible artists curated by @legacybros. 

I hope to see you there as I discuss the art of emotion and finding beauty in the darkness. 

Tickets available now. Link in bio

When it comes to art, there are no rules. Art and creativity  are subjective. Since I started my journey, I’ve ruly enjoyed  creating something breathtaking out of the simplest of materials. Which is why I’ve often found myself using a plain wall or seamless backdrop to set the scene of whatever image I’m creating. By doing this, I’m able to use the human form and whatever prop of choice to effectively communicate the emotion / vision of the concept. 

This isn’t say that using elaborate sets, props, and lighting doesn’t have its benefits. This is merely a reminder that it can be beneficial to revert back to basics and find inspiration in the simplicities of life.

What does it mean to be rooted?
What does it mean to be free? 

These are two questions that were brought up when in discussion with @waynesflight - These questions  played the strings of my soul. 

Sherman, myself, and I’m sure many others have been undergoing the process of releasing things that are no longer of service, unlearning, letting go of the past while becoming introspective and learning the depth of our being. This process is challenging, painful, and can get dark at times.

However, once on the other side, the growth and light that is felt and seen is unmatched. A feeling of liberation, peace, and freedom of the soul brings you back home to yourself.

These images are a representation of said journey. 

Art Commission for @waynesflight

We love, love. Whether it’s love for a significant other, a friend, family, or most importantly love for yourself. Having love in your life is a blessing like no other.

We’re all navigating this human experience together.

It is said that those we come into contact with, form a connection with, are able to reflect the parts of ourselves we need to learn from. 

As if living in a house of mirrors. Through my experience, I have come to learn and know this to be true. 

What are your thoughts? 

@legacybros you are a being of light on this earth. They way you’ve dedicate your life to being of service to others through your love, kinship, and  expertise of Art History is inspiring, revolutionary, and needed. We can all learn something from you.

It’s time let go and fly to new heights

Thank you and always remember to, 

Trust in your voice 
Trust in your vision
Trust in your story

Lost Boy [ photo series ]

As a child Peter Pan was one of my favorite Disney movies. The idea of never growing up, flying, and having a pixie as a bestie — who wouldn’t want that at such a young age. 

Maybe it was because I was an only child and often got lost in my imagination. Creating realities that only I could see. They kept me safe, kept me entertained, and kept the wander. 

I was always one that believed in the impossible, in the unknown, and in fantasy. I still do. 

Whose to say what’s real and what isn’t? It’s all a matter a perspective.

Here’s to the days spent in Neverland

Where do you go when you feel lost? 

In frame: @thefaceofdon

Recently I had to remind myself why I started my journey in photography so many years ago. Below is a short list: 

• To visually communicate emotion
• To showcase the beauty in the darkness
• To inspire others
• To show the inner workings of my imagination 
• For the love it. 

At times there are moments when what used to be our passion starts to feel like work and becomes a chore. It is in that very instant we must remind ourselves of the bigger picture, of the “why.” Then, do what we can to get back there. 

Oddly enough, I feel this everytime I shave my head. It’s brings me back to myself. To who I am at the core. For so long I placed a large piece of my identity in my hair, as many of us do. Shaving my head has become a ritual of release, each time opening my crown chakra to the universe and relearn something that was once lost or hidden. 

If you’ve made it this far through the caption I am grateful for you taking time out of your day to take in a portion of my story. 

So now I ask you, why did you start your journey?

The Darkness [ photo series ]

There comes a time when the darkness must be purged from the body. Although it has been with you for lifetimes, it no longer serves you. Previous way of thinking, the beliefs you had about yourself, bad habits… let it all go. 

It can be a painful process, releasing everything you once held so close.  Especially when unaware of what awaits you on the other side. This process is ongoing, a continuous cleanse of the mind, body, and spirit. There’s nothing like the first time. That initial gut wrenching pain nobody could have ever prepared you for. However, after that you begin to look forward to it. You can feel the signs and know what to look for when it’s time for another purge. 

A state of peace comforts you as you realize this is a natural release. Welcome to a higher state of being. You’ve ascended.

Boys Don’t Cry

Why is that society has conditioned us to teach boys at such a young age that vulnerability and emotional awareness is a sign of weakness? Society tells us that boys should be strong and keep their emotions hidden. 

Crying is forbidden…

Bottling up the pain, the experienced trauma and placing it to the side is what “Men” do… Eventhough it’s increasingly harmful to the psyche and can become stored in the body. Which can turn into physical ailments, unhealthy habits, and harmful projection onto others. 

Safe spaces need to be created with family, loved ones, friends, community, and most importantly yourself. The emotion must be experienced and flow through you.  Allow yourself the opportunity to feel the sadness, feel the pain, and work through the trauma. It’s not easy and it’s a continuous practice but, the growth and love you’ll experience on the other side is unmatched.

Varies from person to person, circumstance, timing, etc… Yet, it’s completely necessary. Releasing old thought patterns, ways of being, and laying down one’s burdens is an experience that can instantly lift one’s spirit. Opening yourself to the new awaiting journey. 

Whether that process is writing, speaking to the universe, taking a bath, or shaving your head in a field of dandelions and then dancing with the sunrise… Cleansing is necessary for growth.

As I was embracing a moment of stillness this morning.
Writing…
I couldn’t help but notice the breathtaking light peaking through the bathroom window. 
Without hesitation I was overcome by inspiration. 
Grabbed my camera and tripod. 
No concept, no idea. 
Just spontaneous inspiration.

Your mind, body, soul, and spirit are your most beautiful creative project.

Gentle reminder: you are constantly changing, evolving, and learning  intricate nuances about yourself daily. Give yourself grace and schedule time to rest.

- I was told when I was younger that my life would be full of changes/ overcoming frequent “rebirths”. I well this year around the sun was just that. This was one of the hardest years for me ❤️‍🩹. I lost myself this year… real bad. After running from my demons, I got them in control (they work for me now 💅🏾). Here is what they taught me:
1. I am hella sexy with clothes off but just as sexy with them on.
2. I don’t need the approval from other, just mySelf.
3. You can forgive, but never forget how that pain felt.
4. Keep the bar as high as possible and those that are meant to be will be.
5. I am a gorgeous model and any brand/agency will be/ is blessed to have me 🤌🏽💨
6. Remain humble and always be Deon Walton 💕
